course_description: This foundational course introduces students to the concept of clinical integration of health promotion, health maintenance, diagnosis and treatment of common, acute, and chronic Women's Health and Gender-Related (WHGR) conditions beginning in puberty and extending across the lifespan.
prerequisites: NRSG 701D and NRSG 704D and NRSG 706D as prerequisites, NRSG 763D as co-requisite, or equivalent transfer credit.
